    <h2>Tecoma — Dandenong Ranges, Timber Cottages, Puffing Billy Country, Cold Misty Winters</h2>
    <div class="local-box"><p>Tecoma is a small Dandenong Ranges community situated alongside the Puffing Billy railway between Belgrave and Upwey, with a residential character shaped by timber cottages, weatherboard homes and period properties in a heavily forested, cool-climate environment. The Dandenong Ranges experience some of Melbourne's coldest and wettest winters at elevation, and the open fireplace is the primary heat source in many of Tecoma's older homes. Heavy winter use means significant creosote build-up in flues that are not regularly swept, making annual professional cleaning essential for both safety and performance.

We service Tecoma as part of our Dandenong Ranges run.</p></div>
